2008-01-17 21:29  robert

	* src/vpb/ThreadPool.cpp: Reduced the default number of queued
	  operations in the ThreadPool's queue to 64 to help keep a lid on
	  memory usage

2008-01-17 19:48  robert

	* src/vpb/ThreadPool.cpp: Tweaked the default of the
	  ThreadPool::run() throttling so that it would allow
	  128 operations to be queued at any one time, and to use a 1/2
	  second sleep to
	  wait for the pool's own threads to catch up.

2008-01-17 19:20  robert

	* include/vpb/ThreadPool, src/vpb/ThreadPool.cpp: Added throttling
	  of the calls to ThreadPool::run to limit the number of operations
	  that the queue will permit.

